=== TASK ===
# User Profile Page

## Overview
Build a robust, secure, and user-friendly User Profile Page that serves as the personal account management hub for studio users. This page orchestrates personal details, profile customization, 2FA, session management, connected OAuth apps, password reset/change flows, and hooks into signup/login with options for SSO (OAuth) and standard email/password. It also ties into the Studio Settings & Team Management page and the Studio Dashboard for a cohesive administrative experience. The UI must be responsive, accessible, and align with the Archject visual design language and design system.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A Personal Account Management interface for a user within a design studio workspace. It consolidates user identity, security, and connected integrations in one centralized surface.

Goals:
- Allow users to view and edit their profile details (name, email, role, company), upload and manage a profile picture, and manage connected apps (OAuth integrations).
- Provide secure session management: list active sessions/devices, revoke access tokens, and rotate tokens as needed with secure storage considerations.
- Offer secure password management: allow password change and a tokenized, rate-limited password reset flow with reset links and expiration policies.
- Support optional Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) via SMS or authenticator apps for enhanced security, particularly for enterprise customers.
- Support secure sign-up and login flows for studio users, including SSO (OAuth) and standard email/password, with a clear UX for enabling SSO.
- Include a Delete Account action with multiple confirmation steps to prevent accidental deletion.
- Tie into Settings & Team Management (branding, emails, subscriptions, integrations) and provide quick navigation to the Studio Dashboard for project insights.

UI elements and how they look:
- Profile Info section: Avatar (with upload capability), name, email, role, company, and a compact status badge if applicable (e.g., 2FA enabled).
- Security section: Change password button, 2FA enable/disable toggle and configuration (SMS or authenticator app), list of active sessions with device names, IPs, and last activity; action to revoke sessions; token rotation indicator.
- Connected Accounts: List of OAuth providers (e.g., Google, Microsoft, GitHub), status (connected/disconnected), connect/revoke actions, and the ability to add/remove connections.
- Password Management: Secure password field for changes, a “Reset Password” mechanism (triggering a tokenized link with expiration), and rate-limiting indicators (e.g., cooldown timer after retries).
- 2FA Section: Setup flow, QR code or secret key for authenticator apps, SMS number management, backup codes, recovery options, and failure modes (e.g., backup code usage).
- Sign-up / Login hints: Contextual guidance for enterprise users about SSO availability and how to enable it.
- Delete Account: Prominent warning with irreversible action, require re-entry of email/username and a final confirmation step before deletion.

Visual guidance:
- Follow the provided color palette and typography; use card-based sections with clear titles, muted secondary text, and right-aligned action controls.
- Consistent left-side navigation with a collapsible architecture for related settings.
- Emphasize accessibility: high contrast text, keyboard navigability, and ARIA labeling where appropriate.

## Components to Build
- UserProfilePage (Container)
  - Subcomponents: ProfileCard, SecurityCard, SessionsCard, ConnectedAccountsCard, PasswordResetCard, TwoFAWidget, DeleteAccountCard
- ProfileCard
  - Elements: Avatar uploader, Name input, Email input, Role selector, Company input, Save/Cancel actions
- SecurityCard
  - Elements: ChangePasswordButton, 2FAToggle (Enable/Disable), 2FAConfigurator (modal), SessionsOverview
- SessionsCard
  - Elements: ActiveSessionsList (Device, IP, LastActive, RevokeButton), RotateTokenButton
- ConnectedAccountsCard
  - Elements: ProviderList (ProviderName, ConnectedStatus, ConnectButton, RevokeButton)
- PasswordManagement
  - Elements: PasswordField (Current, New, Confirm), ResetPasswordLink, RateLimitIndicator
- TwoFAWidget
  - Elements: SetupFlowModal (QR code/secret key, backup codes), SMS setup, Authenticator app setup, Recovery codes
- DeleteAccountCard
  - Elements: WarningMessage, Email ConfirmationInput, ConfirmButton, CancelButton
- Settings & QuickNavBar (shared)
  - Elements: Quick links to Profile, Security, Sessions, Connected Accounts, Password, 2FA, Delete, with breadcrumb support
- StudioNavigationSidebar (shared)
  - Elements: Sections for Dashboard, Settings & Team Management, User Profiles (active when on profile page)
- ConfirmationModal
  - Generic confirmation for irreversible actions (e.g., account deletion, session revocation)

Technical details:
- Data display formats: human-friendly dates for LastActive, serial numbers for session tokens
- Progress indicators: for long-running actions (e.g., re-auth or token rotation)

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Build a responsive, accessible React (or framework-equivalent) SPA component structure with: 
  - 12-column grid layout, consistent card spacing, and a left-hand persistent sidebar
  - State management for user profile, security settings, sessions, connected accounts, and 2FA configuration
  - Form validation with real-time feedback and inline validation messages
  - Secure file upload for profile pictures with client-side validation (type/size) and preview
  - Modals for 2FA setup, password reset, and delete confirmation
  - API call integration hooks (fetch/axios or equivalent) with appropriate error handling, loading states, and retry logic
  - Keyboard accessibility, focus management, and ARIA roles
  - Design system adherence: components, spacing, typography, and color usage as per Visual Style

### Backend
- Implement APIs and DB structures to support:
  - User profile CRUD: fetch and update personal details and avatar URL
  - Session management: list active sessions, revoke session, rotate tokens, and session metadata
  - Password management: request password reset (generate token with expiration and rate-limit), reset password via token, change password
  - 2FA management: enable/disable 2FA, setup flows for authenticator apps and SMS, verify codes, rotate backup codes
  - Connected accounts (OAuth): list connected providers, connect new provider, revoke provider access
  - Account deletion: irreversible delete flow with proper audit logging and cascade considerations
  - SSO/Signup/Login: endpoints to support standard email/password, OAuth sign-in/up, and enterprise SSO configuration
  - Security/storage: ensure hashed tokens, encryption at rest for sensitive data, and token rotation practices
- Data models (schemas):
  - User: id, name, email, avatarUrl, role, company, preferredTheme, twoFA-enabled:boolean, createdAt, updatedAt
  - Sessions: id, userId, deviceName, ipAddress, lastActive, tokenHash, revoked:boolean
  - OAuthConnections: id, userId, provider (e.g., google, github), connectorUserId, connectedAt
  - PasswordResetTokens: id, userId, tokenHash, expiresAt, used:boolean
  - TwoFASettings: id, userId, method (sms|authenticator), secret, phoneNumber, otpBackupCodes[]
  - AuditLog: id, userId, action, target, timestamp, metadata
  - BrandingSettings (for studio, linked from Settings & Team Management): logos, emailTemplates
- Validation and error handling: server-side validation with clear error codes; client displays friendly messages

### Integration
- Frontend communicates with backend via REST/GraphQL endpoints (design endpoints clearly and consistently)
- Secure file uploads flow with signed URLs or streaming uploads; avatar stored in a secure media store
- Authentication context/session: include user token in requests; handle token refresh when needed
- Cross-page navigation: ensure state is preserved when moving between Profile, Settings, and Dashboard
- Feature flags: 2FA and SSO availability may be toggled per studio or enterprise plan; handle gracefully in UI

## User Experience Flow
- Access:
  - User logs in or SSO into Studio workspace
  - From the app shell, navigate to Settings > User Profile or directly to Profile Page
- Profile editing:
  - User updates name, email, role, company, and avatar; clicks Save; success toast shown
- 2FA setup:
  - User toggles 2FA on; chooses authenticator app or SMS; follows on-screen steps (QR scan or code entry, backup codes generated)
  - User verifies code; upon success, 2FA is enabled; can reconfigure or disable from Security section
- Sessions:
  - User reviews Active Sessions, revokes any undesired sessions; token rotation occurs for revoked sessions
- Connected Accounts:
  - User views OAuth providers; can connect new providers or revoke existing connections
- Password management:
  - User can change password via current/new; or request password reset from a “Forgot password?” link; reset email token is sent with expiration and rate limiting
- Deletion:
  - User initiates Delete Account; confirmation modal requires re-entering email, warning message, and a final confirmation step
- Navigation:
  - Quick access to Studio Dashboard and Settings & Team Management for branding, subscriptions, and integrations
- Responsive behavior:
  - On tablet/phone, the sidebar collapses into a hamburger menu; cards stack with preserved content order; modals remain accessible and readable

## Technical Specifications
- Data Models: See Backend section for schemas and relationships
- API Endpoints (Routes and Methods):
  - GET /api/user/profile -> fetch user profile
  - PUT /api/user/profile -> update profile details (name, email, role, company, avatarUrl)
  - POST /api/user/profile/avatar -> upload avatar (or PATCH with avatar)
  - GET /api/user/sessions -> list active sessions
  - POST /api/user/sessions/:id/revoke -> revoke a session
  - POST /api/user/sessions/rotate -> rotate all tokens or specific token
  - POST /api/user/password/change -> change current password
  - POST /api/user/password/reset/request -> request reset token (rate-limited)
  - POST /api/user/password/reset/confirm -> reset password using token
  - POST /api/user/2fa/enable -> enable 2FA
  - POST /api/user/2fa/disable -> disable 2FA
  - POST /api/user/2fa/setup/authenticator -> setup authenticator (TOTP) with secret and QR
  - POST /api/user/2fa/setup/sms -> configure SMS 2FA
  - POST /api/user/2fa/verify -> verify 2FA code
  - GET /api/user/connections -> list OAuth connections
  - POST /api/user/connections/:provider/connect -> connect provider
  - DELETE /api/user/connections/:provider -> revoke provider
  - DELETE /api/user -> delete account (requires confirmation)
  - GET /api/settings/branding -> fetch studio branding
  - PATCH /api/settings/branding -> update studio branding
  - GET /api/settings/subscription -> fetch studio subscription
  - GET /api/settings/integrations -> fetch studio integrations
  - POST /api/signup -> signup (with options for OAuth or email/password)
  - POST /api/auth/login -> login (email/password)
  - POST /api/auth/sso -> initiate SSO flow
- Security:
  - Use OAuth2/OIDC tokens for API authentication; short-lived access tokens with refresh tokens
  - Passwords stored with strong hashing ( bcrypt/Argon2)
  - 2FA secrets stored encrypted at rest; rotateable U2F keys or TOTP secrets
  - CSRF protection for state-changing operations
  - Rate limiting on sensitive endpoints (password reset requests, login attempts)
  - Audit logging for profile changes, 2FA changes, session revocations, deletions
- Validation:
  - Email format validation; name constraints; role and company field validations
  - Avatar upload: image type (jpeg/png/webp), max size (e.g., 5MB)
  - Password strength validation on change
  - 2FA code validation window (e.g., +/- 1 time step)
  - OAuth provider tokens and connections validation

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] User can view and update their profile (name, email, role, company) and upload avatar; changes persist and reflect immediately
- [ ] 2FA can be enabled with authenticator app (TOTP) or SMS; codes validate correctly; backup codes are generated and stored
- [ ] Active sessions are listed with accurate metadata; user can revoke individual sessions and rotate tokens
- [ ] Password reset flow is secure: tokenized link sent, expiration enforced, rate-limited requests
- [ ] Connected OAuth providers are listable; providers can be connected or revoked; UI updates accordingly
- [ ] Sign-up/Login supports standard email/password and SSO flows; enterprise SSO hints and controls present
- [ ] Delete Account action requires deliberate confirmation and cannot be completed accidentally
- [ ] UI adheres to the design system: color, typography, spacing, component behavior, and responsive rules
- [ ] All endpoints include appropriate error handling and return user-friendly messages; loading and error states are visible
- [ ] Accessible (ARIA), keyboard-navigable, and mobile-responsive with proper focus handling

